<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-136-139 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 799 274</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  June 3 1991 n323 p48(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The new credo: customer service. (product support is the key tosuccess in the software industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Moran, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Large software vendors are increasing their revenues by providingsoftware packages and services to information systems (IS)clients.andP;  Professional services generated 10 percent of softwarecompanies' revenues in the past, but some large firms have seenthis figure increase to 50 percent.andP;  The percentage is notexpected to increase significantly in the future, but the serviceswill continue to create new business and to sell more software.andO;Many customers want vendors to design systems, act as projectmanagers, install systems and train personnel.andP;  Prices forconsulting in areas such as personnel training and projectmanagement are high, but IS clients earn back the costs becausesystems are installed faster and designed better.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Customer RelationsSoftware packagesComputer industryInformation systemsSupport ServicesTrends.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>